The paper discusses privacy concerns in data mining and statistical analysis, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also proposes a novel entropy-based security measure that can be applied to any generalization, restriction, or data modification technique, which involves database systems (cs.DB) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also evaluates and compares popular methods such as query restriction, sampling, and noise addition, which are related to data structures and algorithms (cs.DS) and information theory (cs.IT).
